        "uuid": "88c1977c_12c88237",
        "filename": "tools/perf-puppeteer/canvaskit-skottie-frames-load.html",
        "patchSetId": 28
      },
      "lineNbr": 1,
      "author": {
        "id": 5145
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-04-30T18:07:38Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "This uses performance.now() and measures timings here. This is what the first iteration of skottie-was-perf.html did as well (but used frame numbers not clock time).\nThis was changed to use chrome tracing instead because of the reasons in https://bugs.chromium.org/p/skia/issues/detail?id\u003d9237\nYou probably do not care about this right now, but something to keep in mind if we want to ever compare this approach with other frameworks that might use SVG backend (like lottie-web).",
      "revId": "db8196822b24bb5e47f8d58217daa696c13bcf92",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "3050d437_95f39a5f",
        "filename": "tools/perf-puppeteer/canvaskit-skottie-frames-load.html",
        "patchSetId": 28
      },
      "lineNbr": 1,
      "author": {
        "id": 5395
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-05-01T14:00:45Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "The metrics I am measuring here are not intended to replace the existing SkottieWASM benchmarks. Nor is the goal for these metrics to compare against LottieWeb. The goal is to get realistic numbers for specifically CanvasKit.",
      "parentUuid": "88c1977c_12c88237",
      "revId": "db8196822b24bb5e47f8d58217daa696c13bcf92",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "0ad12bd9_bbce89d8",
        "filename": "tools/perf-puppeteer/canvaskit-skottie-frames-load.html",
        "patchSetId": 28
      },
      "lineNbr": 4,
      "author": {
        "id": 5145
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-04-30T18:07:38Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "This is an interesting approach, have you chatted with Florin about this? (just to get another perspective).\nI also remember frames being particularly noisy at start (during setup) and at the end (during teardown) so we ran multiple loops and took data from the middle.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 4,
        "startChar": 34,
        "endLine": 4,
        "endChar": 96
      },
      "revId": "db8196822b24bb5e47f8d58217daa696c13bcf92",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": false
    },
